body:
After this change, `TestPipeline#run()` looks like so:

```java
public PipelineResult run() {
   ...
    try {
      ...
      pipelineResult = super.run();
    } catch (RuntimeException exc) {
      Throwable cause = exc.getCause();
      if (cause instanceof AssertionError) {
        throw (AssertionError) cause;
      } else {
        throw exc;
      }
    }

    enforcement.get().afterPipelineExecution();
    ...
  }
```

So in case of an exception in `super.run()`, I would not expect the flow to reach `afterPipelineExecution()`, which makes the kind of test you mention quite challenging on one hand, but satisfying your requirement kind of "by definition" on the other hand.

Edit:
Having looked again at `afterPipelineExecution()`, it seems that you're interested in generating an exception particularly in `recordPipelineNodes()`, which other than via `afterPipelineExecution()`, can be reached via an alternative path: `afterUserCodeFinished() => verifyPipelineExecution() => else branch of if`. If so, then we'll need a way to `throw` in `recordPipelineNodes()`, any ideas how to do that?
